<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>DATA:  It is perhaps not what we would understand as a vessel, sir. The dimensions this one occupies allows them to be, well, to be in several places at once. But they consider this entire star cluster to be theirs. It was probably unwise of us to attempt to place a human colony in this area. Of course, there are three thousand four other planets in this star cluster in which we could have colonised. The largest and closest</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>PICARD:  Data, don't babble.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>DATA:  Babble, sir? I'm not aware that I ever babble, sir. It may be that from time to time I have considerable information to communicate, and you may question the way I organise it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>PICARD:  Please, organise it into brief answers to my questions. We have very little time. Do they accept our presence at this planet?</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>DATA:  Undecided, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>PICARD:  Data, please, feel free to volunteer any important information.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>DATA:  I volunteer that they are now observing us, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>PICARD:  To judge what kind of life forms we are?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>DATA:  No, it is more curiosity, sir. I doubt that they expect us to abide by their value systems.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>PICARD:  Do they know of our Prime Directive?</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>DATA:  They know everything I know, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>PICARD:  And, if we were to violate the Prime Directive, how</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  That's not a fair question.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>PICARD:  How would they react?</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>DATA:  It would be a case of judging us by our own rules, sir. If we violate our own Prime Directive, they might consider us to be deceitful and untrustworthy. You do recall they cautioned us not to interfere with their children below. What has happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  The Edo want to execute my son. I will not allow that to happen, Jean-Luc.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>DATA:  Most interesting, sir. The emotion of motherhood, compared to all others felt by</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  Shut up!</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Beverly storms out</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>DATA:  You were right, sir. I do tend to babble.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 41255.9. Whatever the object or vessel in orbit with us, it hangs there like a nemesis. It is one thing to communicate with something mysterious, but it is quite another to be silently observed by it. I am concerned whether it understands the same concept of reason that we do?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Lounge</td></tr>
<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>DATA:  You sent for me, sir?</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>PICARD:  Let's have more talk, Data.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>DATA:  Yes, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>PICARD:  Sit down.</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>DATA:  What level of communication, sir?</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>PICARD:  Any. My apologies for saying that you babbled.</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>DATA:  But I do, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>PICARD:  You also see things in a way we do not, but as they truly are. I need help, my friend. I cannot permit that boy or any member of this vessel be sacrificed. The Prime Directive never intended that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>DATA:  The problem, sir, is there. (the Edo vessel) Although they've learned of the Prime Directive from my mind, how will they evaluate it? How do they reason? What are their values? Remember their warning to us, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>PICARD:  Exactly. How do I explain my refusing to obey their laws down there. Not permitting the Crusher boy to be executed. And by so doing do I endanger this vessel and more than a thousand other lives?</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>DATA:  Would you choose one life over one thousand, sir?</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>PICARD:  I refuse to let arithmetic decide questions like that. Did you learn anything about the relationship between that and the Edo? Why are they so certain it's a god?</td></tr>

<tr id="L365"><td><a href="#L365">365</a></td><td>DATA:  Any sufficiently advanced life form would appear to others to be that, sir. But when they were probing my thoughts, Captain, I could feel that whatever they are now, they once existed in this dimension, just as we do. Perhaps in the same kind of flesh and blood form. Since then, however, they have evolved considerably. Their present existence in multi-dimensions no doubt has advantages we do not understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L366"><td><a href="#L366">366</a></td><td>PICARD:  Then in some earlier flesh and blood form they might have shared our kind of values.</td></tr>

<tr id="L367"><td><a href="#L367">367</a></td><td>DATA:  We know the Edo share them, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L368"><td><a href="#L368">368</a></td><td>PICARD:  Why would such an advanced thing feel obliged to protect the Edo?</td></tr>

<tr id="L369"><td><a href="#L369">369</a></td><td>DATA:  Perhaps the Edo are a child race by comparison. Possibly a race which those life forms have planted here. Much as we plant human colonies on Class-M planets.</td></tr>

<tr id="L370"><td><a href="#L370">370</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Crusher enters</td></tr>

<tr id="L371"><td><a href="#L371">371</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  Having fulfilled my professional obligations regarding Commander Data</td></tr>

<tr id="L372"><td><a href="#L372">372</a></td><td>PICARD:  You now request permission to beam down to the planet. Permission granted. You can accompany me while I try and resolve this. And you should know that whatever the cost, I will not allow them to execute your son.</td></tr>

<tr id="L373"><td><a href="#L373">373</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  Thank you, sir.</td></tr>

